# Posttraumatic Stress Disorder is Associated With Alpha Dysrhythmia Across the Visual Cortex and the Default Mode Network
**Autores**: Kevin Clancy
**Año**: Not specified
**Journal**: Biological Psychiatry, 87 (2020) S211. doi:10.1016/j.biopsych.2020.02.549
**DOI/Link**: N/A

## Abstract
Not found

## Key Findings
Conclusions: Post-trauma resting heart rate is associated
with the experience of peritraumatic dissociation and is
moderated by a past history of trauma exposure. Further
investigation of the physiological underpinnings of peri-
traumatic dissociation is warranted.
